<h3>Setting up Petal</h3>

<h4>Quick Start</h4>

<p>Include the line below inside the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> of your HTML file. Place it before any other site page stylesheets.</p>

<div class="code-block">
{{#markdown}}
``` html
<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="https://petalcdn.shakr.com/edge/petal.min.css">
```
{{/markdown}}
</div>

<p>The CDN link will provide the latest minified pre-built version of Petal with default settings.</p>

<p>Now you can use all the Petal classes and styles in your project's HTML file.</p>

<p>If you want to customize options and personalize Petal style for your project, you will need to build Petal manually. Head to <a href="custom.html">Custom Building</a> for guide and recommendations on integrating Petal into your project.</p>